From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 19:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] libvmaf: add libvmaf_sycl filter (zero-copy VAAPI/QSV import)

Introduces a dedicated `libvmaf_sycl` FFmpeg filter that consumes
QSV/oneVPL frames (`AVFrame->data[3] -> mfxFrameSurface1*`),
extracts the underlying VA surface handle, and routes it through
`vmaf_sycl_import_va_surface` for zero-copy DMA-BUF import on the
Level Zero / SYCL compute queue. Avoids the
`hwdownload,format=yuv420p` round-trip that the regular `libvmaf`
filter forces when input is hardware-decoded.

Pairs with the C-API surfaces in
libvmaf/include/libvmaf/libvmaf_sycl.h:
  - vmaf_sycl_state_init / vmaf_sycl_import_state
  - vmaf_sycl_import_va_surface
  - vmaf_sycl_dmabuf_import (used internally by import_va_surface)
  - vmaf_sycl_wait_compute (per-frame synchronisation barrier)
  - vmaf_sycl_profiling_enable / _get_string (optional)

Closes T7-28 in the fork backlog. Companion to the existing
0003-libvmaf-wire-sycl-backend-selector.patch (which adds the
sycl_device option to the regular libvmaf filter); together the
two patches give users:

  * libvmaf=sycl_device=N      — software frames + SYCL compute
  * libvmaf_sycl=...           — QSV/VAAPI hwdec + zero-copy SYCL

Validated end-to-end on Intel Arc A380 with VAAPI hwdec via QSV
oneVPL. Patch is on top of 0001-0004 (post-vulkan-selector
baseline).

---
